OL,3,CHow big a health hazard is mould
OL,4,Cgrowing in London Underground stations?
OL,6,FDaniel Henk, Myologist at University
OL,7,Fof Bath added: "I was a little
OL,8,Fsurprised by it in the stations we
OL,9,Fwere going, how frequent there were
OL,10,Fthese damp patches that had damage and
OL,11,Fmaybe some fungal presence.
OL,13,F"Maybe there's more than I expected. I
OL,14,Fwas taken a little bit aside by just
OL,15,Fhow much I saw of damp damage. I think
OL,16,Fthere is a maintenance issue there."
OL,18,FITV News London made a Freedom of
OL,19,FInformation request to Transport for
OL,20,FLondon about its mould.
