OL,3,CHow big a health hazard is mould
OL,4,Cgrowing in London Underground stations?
OL,6,FThey told us they don't have any
OL,7,F"significant growth" in public facing
OL,8,Fareas and added there was no specific
OL,9,Fbudget for dealing with mould.
OL,11,FDaniel Henk added: "I would be very
OL,12,Fsurprised if they weren't concerned
OL,13,Fwith mould. It should be part of what
OL,14,Fthey always are considering.
OL,16,F"I would say consider the fungi. Take
OL,17,Fthe fungal component of what they do
OL,18,Fseriously. I wouldn't say that it's an
OL,19,Fissue that needs to be raised to red
OL,20,Falert for them.
